    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;The estimation of the motion of an elongated, slanted segment (here moving horizontally to the right) on a limited area (such as the receptive field of a neuron) leads to ambiguous velocity measurements compared to physical motion: it’s the aperture problem. We represent as arrows the velocity vectors that are most likely detected by a motion energy model; hue indicates direction angle. Introducing predictive coding resolves the aperture problem.&#34;
